# Build context excludes. The Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so anything not listed
# here ends up inside the image — including in the final runtime layer.

# --- Secrets: never bake these into an image layer ---
# The API loads config through lib/env.ts (`import 'dotenv/config'`), which reads
# a .env from the working directory if one exists. Copying the host's .env in
# would both embed production secrets (DB password, VAPID private key, Cloudflare
# token) in a distributable layer and make the container's real configuration
# invisible to `docker inspect`. Config comes from compose.server.yml instead —
# every key the schema reads is declared there or as a Dockerfile ENV.
.env
.env.*
.secrets/
*.keystore
*.jks

# --- Not needed to build or run the server ---
.git
.github
.devcontainer
.claude
docs

# The Android client is built by CI, never by this image, and its generated
# android/ directory is large.
apps/mobile

# Installed in-image by `npm ci`; copying host modules over that would break the
# Prisma engine match (the host may not be debian-openssl-3.0.x).
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Built in-image; a stale local copy must not shadow it.
**/dist
**/.vite
